 

Answer: 
- The Construction Industry Promotion Board of Government of Malaysia has applied analytic models to forecast the nation-wide supply and demand of construction steel products and uncover the root cause of industry crisis.
- The methodology used for this purpose is Time Series Regression with industry and macroeconomic data.
- The challenges faced during this process include multiple products, differential regulatory price controls across products, and actual steel consumption data not readily available.
- The value delivered includes accurate forecasting models to predict supply and demand for different economic scenarios and pinpointing of the root cause of industry crisis such as product cannibalization resulting in supply shortages.<|im_end|>